race.description: Catalina Country Club Country Boosted Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: WONDERFUL MISTAKE (9) went close when switching wide in the straight, with the winners coming up the inside at this track last time out. Not willing to jump off her on the back of that effort as she gives the impression the rise in trip is going to be perfect. Draw is sticky, but there looks to be plenty more under the hood. LYSANDER (5) wasn't far away over 1425m here last start and comes back in trip today. That is the slight niggle, though he retains Guymer and the draw is perfect for him. Should be close to the speed on settling down and will be tough to catch. BOOM IN THE DARK (2) got back to form here last start when closing off strongly to score in a photo finish. Out in trip won't be an issue and he can finish over the top of them once again. JAZZ ALL KNIGHT (3) is hard to knock on her recent form and has to be included. OUR LITTLE STAR (4) is suspect at the trip but she's racing well and is not out of this.
